        "text": "\"Von Foerster says that \"self organizing systems do not feed only in order, they find also noise in their menu.\" (1960) This Foersterian principle is different from SCHRÖDINGER 's disorder, which is, statistically, order. But the Foersterian principle, as well emphasized by G. GÜNTHER (1962), establishes the synthesis: the \"Aufhebung\" (overtaking) of order-from-order and of order-from-disorder is mechanicist, \"order- from-disorder is regularity, order-from noise is [[Novelty]], or [[Creativity]]\" (MORIN, 1972, p.185)."
